<TITLE> Selim Al-Din to be moved to Bangkok hospital Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 14 (bdnews24.com)  Critically ill playwright Selim Al-Din will be transferred to a Thailand hospital Monday afternoon for better treatment, a LabAid spokesman said. LabAid media coordinator Mesbah Azad told bdnews24.com that Selim would be sent to the Bangkok Heart Institute at Bangkok General Hospital. "The time is not yet fixed, any time between 3pm and 4pm," he said. "The noted playwright will be taken to Bangkok as per his relatives' wishes," Mesbah added. Selim's condition deteriorated Sunday and remained unchanged up to Monday morning. The Jahangirnagar University drama and dramatics professor was rushed to BIRDEM Friday evening after suffering respiratory trouble. He was transferred to LabAid after doctors diagnosed cardiac problems. bdnews24.co
